						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Undated. In Tamiḻ-Brāhmi characters. (2nd cent. B.C.)</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription mentions that Eḷa-a Ataṉ was a cloth <hi rend="italic">(aṟavai)</hi> merchant from Veṇpaḷi-i. Though there is no mention about his endowment, it can be presumed that he made some gift to the mendicants in the cavern. At the end of the inscription is carved a symbol similar to the one found in No. 74.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">ETE.</hi> (2014), No. 46, p. 447.</p>						

						</summary>
